header.gameNote: DUEL IN THE DESERT AT LUBBOCK TX

article.headline: Texas Tech 64, Oregon St. 60
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- David Tairu scored 19 points to lead Texas Tech past Oregon State in the Duel in the Desert tournament Sunday. The Beavers battled back from a double-digit deficit to pull even with the Red Raiders (3-0) at 50-50 with about four minutes remaining in the game. The score stayed close until Tairu and Mike Singletary hit back-to-back 3s to put the game out of reach for Oregon State (1-2). Seth Tarver scored 17 points to lead the Beavers. Tairu, who was named MVP of the tournament, was 6-of-11 from the field and hit four of five from beyond the arc. The Beavers outrebounded the Red Raiders 35 to 23. Joe Burton of Oregon State led with nine rebounds.
